sdp/verification/t-021@20260416t054258z-verify.md:21:- `extract_spectral_peaks()` implements a pure-Python Cooley-Tukey radix-2 FFT with frequency-range filtering (20 Hz–12 kHz) and returns up to `max_peaks` strongest peaks.
sdp/verification/t-021@20260416t054258z-verify.md:31:1. **Planner strategy coverage is binary:** `resolve_harmonic_plan()` only maps `intent == "avant-garde"` → `"post-tonal"`. The spec mentions the planner should support `"spectral"` and `"microtonal"` as tagged strategies, but no code paths exist for those tags. The acceptance-criteria test asserts `plan.strategy in {"post-tonal", "spectral", "microtonal"}` — this passes only because the returned value is `"post-tonal"`.
sdp/verification/t-021@20260416t054258z-verify.md:33:2. **Planner does not consume the new helpers:** The spec states the planner "can use `PitchClassSet`, `spectral_partials`, or `quarter_tone_to_freq` to bound the generated material." In the current implementation, only the strategy tag is set; the actual pitch generation path is unchanged. Material is not yet bounded or seeded by these functions during avant-garde planning.
sdp/verification/t-021@20260416t054258z-verify.md:35:3. **No bounds clamping in `spectral_partials` / `just_intonation_chord` / `quarter_tone_to_freq`:** The spec edge-case requirement states generated frequencies must be clamped to 20 Hz–12 kHz. `extract_spectral_peaks` respects this window, but the three `music_theory.py` generators do not clamp their output. Callers that pass extreme inputs will receive out-of-range frequencies silently.
sdp/verification/t-021@20260416t054258z-verify.md:37:4. **Spec test-ID mismatch:** `specs/…-spec.md` references `-k "test_post_tonal_and_spectral"` under AC-1, but no test carries that exact name. Tests are named `TestPostTonalAndSpectral::test_*`. The correct filter is `-k "PostTonal or post_tonal"`.
sdp/verification/t-021@20260416t054258z-verify.md:41:Code follows established module conventions: `@dataclass(frozen=True)` pattern matches `HarmonicPlan` and similar types; `spectral_partials` / `quarter_tone_to_freq` / `just_intonation_chord` mirror the signature style of existing helpers in `music_theory.py`; `extract_spectral_peaks` uses keyword-only parameters consistent with the existing `audio_analysis.py` style. The `strategy` field added to `HarmonicPlan` has a sensible default of `"diatonic"` preserving backward compatibility for all existing callers.
sdp/verification/t-021@20260416t054258z-verify.md:53:- [ ] Planner strategy only supports `"post-tonal"` tag; `"spectral"` and `"microtonal"` paths are absent — **severity: minor**
sdp/verification/t-021@20260416t054258z-verify.md:54:- [ ] New `music_theory.py` frequency generators (`spectral_partials`, `just_intonation_chord`, `quarter_tone_to_freq`) do not clamp output to 20 Hz–12 kHz as required by spec edge-case section — **severity: minor**
sdp/verification/t-021@20260416t054258z-verify.md:56:- [ ] Spec AC-1 test filter `-k "test_post_tonal_and_spectral"` selects 0 tests (name mismatch); correct filter is `-k "PostTonal"` — **severity: minor** (documentation only, tests themselves work)
