sdp/verification/t-022@20260416t054258z-verify.md:39:**Code content is stub-level.** Every recipe uses an identical `SinOsc.ar(freq)` SynthDef regardless of the technique being described. A granular recipe should use `TGrains` or `GrainBuf`; FM should use carrier/modulator UGen chains; compression should use `CompanderD` or `Compander`; spectral freeze should use `PV_*` UGens; etc. The code examples are currently non-illustrative and would not help a learner understand the named technique.
sdp/verification/t-022@20260416t054258z-verify.md:53:All acceptance criteria are met and all tests pass. The one item worth addressing in a follow-up task: replace the boilerplate SynthDef bodies in each recipe with examples that actually demonstrate the technique (e.g., `TGrains` for granular, `PV_Freeze`/`PV_MagFreeze` for spectral freeze, a carrier+modulator chain for FM, `CompanderD` for compression). This would turn these files from navigational stubs into genuinely useful curriculum references. Consider filing a T-023+ task scoped to "flesh out SuperCollider recipe code examples."
